description.narrative: By 2020, a national child sensitive social protection strategy operationalised in six target provinces, which contributes to Access To Inclusive Social Protection, Access To Inclusive Social Protection (Covid), Child Protection â€“ General, Child Protection â€“ Strengthen Families And Communities, Health And Development In Early Childhood And Adolescence, Promotion Of Care, Mental Health And Psychosocial Well-Being And Justice, Protection From Violence, Exploitation, Abuse And Neglect, Protection From Violence, Exploitation, Abuse And Neglect (Covid), Social Protection And Child Poverty. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Communications, Advocacy And Public Engagement, Community Engagement, Social And Behaviour Change, Data, Research, Evaluation And Knowledge Management, Evaluations, Research And Data, Fostering Innovation And Use Of New Technologies, Innovation, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, Systems Strengthening To Leave No One Behind. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By 2020, the poorest and most marginalised children benefit from a more effective child and social protection system (cash and care)

description.narrative: UNICEF supported the Government to strengthen child protection social service provision. The approved Standard Operating Procedures (SOPs) for case management - developed with UNICEF support - were tested as a model throughout the country enhancing capacity of the social service workforce, including mentorship. Capacity on mental health and psychosocial support;was enhanced through development of referral protocols to address the increasing demand for psychosocial support services by communities including frontline social workers. | Status:Met | As-of Date:12/01/2022
